<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="520" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1542,2035]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1542,1567]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was described recently (
<bibRefCitation author="Roig-Alsina" box="[709,922,1542,1566]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" refString="Roig-Alsina, A. (2000) Claves para las especies argentinas de Centris (Hymenoptera, Apidae), con descripcion de nuevas especies y notas sobre distribucion. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales (nueva serie), 2, 171 - 193." type="journal article" year="2000">
Roig-Alsina, 
<number box="[862,922,1542,1566]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), so its redescription seems redundant. Below are given some diagnostic characters to help the identification of both sexes of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="520" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1542,2035]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1614,1639]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Both sexes with integument and pilosity dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[927,1065,1614,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,509,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,509,1596]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Centris vardyorum Roig-Alsina, 2000. Fig. 25. Female (El Challao, Argentina): Head, frontal view. Fig. 26. Habitus, lateral view. Fig. 27. Male (El Challao, Argentina): Head, frontal view. Fig. 28. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248418/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
Figs. 
<number box="[991,1065,1614,1638]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" value="26.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="25.0">25–28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metasoma with relatively weak metallic bluish violet reflections (
<figureCitation box="[526,703,1650,1674]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,509,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,509,1596]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Centris vardyorum Roig-Alsina, 2000. Fig. 25. Female (El Challao, Argentina): Head, frontal view. Fig. 26. Habitus, lateral view. Fig. 27. Male (El Challao, Argentina): Head, frontal view. Fig. 28. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248418/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
Figs. 
<number box="[589,617,1650,1674]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" value="26.0">26</number>
and 
<number box="[671,703,1650,1674]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Female: fore elaiospathe strongly modified, with short, plumose and very dense pilosity on its ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[662,745,1686,1710]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 34" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,870,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[155,1440,870,1730]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 34. Oil-collecting structures. Figs. 29, 31 and 33. Fore elaiospathes. Figs. 30, 32 and 34. Hind elaiospathes. Figs. 29 and 30. Centris cineraria Smith, 1854. Scale bars 500 µm. Figs. 31 and 32. Centris moldenkei Toro &amp; Chiappa, 1989. Scale bars 200 µm. Figs. 33 and 34. Centris vardyorum Roig-Alsina, 2000. Scale bars 500 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248419/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
Fig. 
<number box="[714,745,1686,1710]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
). These hairs extend throughout the ventral surface of the fore tarsi. 
<collectingCountry box="[215,271,1722,1746]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Hind</collectingCountry>
elaiospathe with the hairs of the primary comb slightly separated, less than their diameters (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1424,1722,1746]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 34" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,870,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[155,1440,870,1730]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 34. Oil-collecting structures. Figs. 29, 31 and 33. Fore elaiospathes. Figs. 30, 32 and 34. Hind elaiospathes. Figs. 29 and 30. Centris cineraria Smith, 1854. Scale bars 500 µm. Figs. 31 and 32. Centris moldenkei Toro &amp; Chiappa, 1989. Scale bars 200 µm. Figs. 33 and 34. Centris vardyorum Roig-Alsina, 2000. Scale bars 500 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248419/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,1722,1746]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eyes red in females and green in males (in live specimens).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
